genresAdvancedInfo.name: harmonica jazz
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Harmonica jazz is a style of jazz music that incorporates the harmonica as a lead instrument. It has a unique sound that blends the bluesy tones of the harmonica with the improvisational elements of jazz. Harmonica jazz can be both upbeat and mellow, and it often features virtuosic solos from the harmonica player.
